 smile. She muffled a yawn and added: “In point of fact, I am the Devil.”

Shy, naive Erwin took this to be a figure of speech, but the lady, lowering her voice, continued as follows:

“Those who imagine me with horns and a thick tail are greatly mistaken. Only once did I appear in that shape, to some Byzantine imbecile, and I really don’t know why it was such a damned success. I am born three or four times every two centuries. In the 1870s, some fifty years ago, I was buried, with pictu